<i>Public Relations Rep</i><br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ullorianlanys.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Llorian Lanys</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(5/27/01 9:22:45 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why dont you use Charm in Planes?</span><hr size=1> Because it generally adds to the confusion of what is going on.  <br>
<br>
Remember there are 24-36 people there, all trying to focus on being on one mob.  There are people trying to debuff mobs, etc etc.<br>
<br>
If a mob is moving around, it triggers ALL sorts of reactions from ALL sorts of people :<br>
<br>
1) The other enchanters dump mana into it trying to Mez it.<br>
<br>
2) The shaman try to slow it<br>
<br>
3) the druids try to snare it<br>
<br>
4) the mages try to malo it <br>
<br>
5) The taunting tanks ( like paladins ) try to stun it so that the enchanters can mez it.<br>
<br>
<br>
ALL of that will happen repeatedly, until ALL of those people realize you have a mob charmed.  Then they will have wasted all of their time and energy trying to do this.  Multiply this by the number of enchanters ( and necros ), on the raid, and you have pure chaos.  The extra damage potential from charm is NOT needed in those situations to help the mob drop faster, so it becomes a parlor trick.  As a parlor trick it is not worth the time and energy of all of those people just so one person can have a little fun.<br>
<br>
There ARE times when charm is a viable tactic to defeating an ubermob... If you are level 60 you can charm and haste a Jugg and send it at trakannon.. the extra damage from a level 57 mob that is hasted DOES make a difference.<br>
<br>
You can do what daeon said, and Use charm against a Mob like the broken golem, or one of the demis, as an expendable tank.  When you do this, it is outlined ahead of time what is going on, and the highest level enchanter is the one doing the charming.  Other than those specific instances, charm on raids should be avoided because of those variables i stated before.<br>
<br>
If you raid with the same people all the time, and it is worked out ahead of time that YOU and only YOU will be charming, that works as well.  Other than that, charm should be reserved for small group raids, raids where mobs are un mezzable ( Kael, Fire giants ), or times when it is discussed ahead of time exactly WHO will do the charming, and exactly what the reason is.<br>
<br>
